    {'id': 'tf_general_t03_pigeon_c', 'topic': 'general', 'type': 'tf', 'difficulty': 5, 'prompt': 'In Mathlib the general pigeonhole principles live in `Mathlib.Combinatorics.Pigeonhole`.', 'answer': True, 'explanation': 'That is where `Finset.exists_ne_map_eq_of_card_lt_of_maps_to` and friends live.'},
    {'id': 'tf_general_t03_pigeon_d', 'topic': 'general', 'type': 'tf', 'difficulty': 5, 'prompt': 'In Lean a proof by contradiction is opened with the tactic `by_contra`.', 'answer': True, 'explanation': '`by_contra h` introduces the negation of the goal as hypothesis `h` and leaves us with `False` to prove.'},
    {'id': 'tf_lambda_00', 'topic': 'lambda', 'type': 'tf', 'difficulty': 2, 'prompt': '(\\x. x x)(\\x. x x) has a normal form.', 'answer': False, 'explanation': 'It is Ω.'},
